    "narrative": "The LawDog lineup faces a challenging slate today, headlined by a formidable matchup against Glasnow. Despite the SP's pedigree, **Geraldo Perdomo** emerges as our strongest play with a 68.41 rating. Batting leadoff against Martin, **Geraldo Perdomo** benefits from a high-leverage lineup slot and a favorable SP xERA of 4.68, making him our primary engine for Runs. **Bryson Stott** also presents a high-floor opportunity (62.02); his profile is bolstered by a wind-out factor and a strong platoon advantage against Cabrera, keeping him firmly in the \"Strong\" start tier despite the overall difficulty of the daily environment.\n\nTargeting our scarcity in stolen bases, we have factored \"Slow SP Delivery\" metrics into our lineup construction. **Matt Chapman** (57.18) and **Jung Hoo Lee** (51.45) receive slight boosts because Glasnow\u2019s delivery timing creates a window for aggressive base running. While **Luis Arraez** (54.16) and **Gleyber Torres** (51.41) hover in the marginal-to-strong range, we are proceeding with caution. **Drew Gilbert** (43.24) and **Wenceel Perez** (45.20) are currently our most precarious starts; their low lineup placement (Order #8) significantly drags down their efficiency, effectively capping their ceiling. We have cleared our bench of all available personnel, as **Jos\u00e9 Ram\u00edrez**, **Cal Raleigh**, **Will Smith**, and **Lawrence Butler** are currently inactive or off-day restricted, leaving no viable pivots for the bottom of our order. Monitor the weather reports closely, as any shift in wind direction could negate the slight boost we\u2019ve afforded **Bryson Stott** in today\u2019s projection model.",
